---
import Welcome from '../components/Welcome.astro';
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';

---

<Layout>
 <div class="flex min-h-screen bg-white dark:bg-slate-900 text-slate-900 dark:text-white">
  <!-- Desktop Sidebar (hidden on small screens) -->
  <aside class="hidden sm:flex w-48 sm:w-56 p-4 flex-col items-center">
    <nav class="flex flex-col gap-3 text-sm font-medium items-center">
      <a href="/" class="hover:opacity-70">Home</a>
      <a href="/projects" class="hover:opacity-70">Projects</a>
      <a href="/contact" class="hover:opacity-70">Contact</a>
    </nav>
  </aside>

  <!-- Mobile Header (hamburger menu, shown only on small screens) -->
  <header class="sm:hidden w-full p-4 flex justify-between items-center bg-white dark:bg-slate-900 border-b border-slate-300 dark:border-slate-700">
    <h1 class="text-lg font-semibold">Aayan</h1>
    <button id="menu-btn" class="text-2xl focus:outline-none">â˜°</button>

    <!-- Hidden mobile menu -->
    <nav
      id="mobile-menu"
      class="hidden absolute top-16 left-0 w-full flex flex-col items-center gap-3 p-4 bg-white dark:bg-slate-900 text-sm"
    >
      <a href="/" class="hover:opacity-70">Home</a>
      <a href="/projects" class="hover:opacity-70">Projects</a>
      <a href="/contact" class="hover:opacity-70">Contact</a>
    </nav>
  </header>


  <section class="w-full text-center mt-16">
    <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-8xl font-bold">aayan shaikh.</h1>
    <p class="text-base sm:text-lg mt-4 opacity-80">
    Shell commands. Circuit boards. Bulding the future. 
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-2xl mx-auto mt-12 px-6 text-lg leading-relaxed">
    <p>
      Hey! I'm Aayan. I like working on embedded systems, Linux, and building cool hardware or software projects.
	</p>

	<p class="py-5">
		I am a undergraduate student at the University of Guelph, studying Computer Engineering (Co-op). 
	</p>


	<p> 
		Some cool projects I've engineered include a custom keyboard designed from scratch, 
		my own development board (think Arduino) featuring LoRa communication and battery managment, 
		and an at-home hydrogen generation system concept (won 1st place!). 
		If this sounds cool, check these projects out in the Projects section!
	</p>


  </section>

  
  </div>

  
</Layout>
